verbose_text: Spermatozoa from boar and mouse utilize the glycerol-3-phosphate shuttle where cytoplasmic glycerol-3-phospate dehydrogenase (cGAP) reduces dihydroxyacetone phosphate (DHAP) to glycerol-3-phosphate (G3P) by oxidizing NADH to NAD +.
evidence: cytoplasmic glycerol-3-phospate dehydrogenase (cGAP) reduces dihydroxyacetone phosphate
